speech.p: I thank the Minister on behalf of members of the Malaya league community in Salisbury, who make a very valuable contribution to the economy of the country.
Motion made, and Question put forthwith (Standing Order No. 177A(3)),

That the East Midlands Regional Grand Committee shall meet in Nottingham on Wednesday 9 September between 2.00 pm and 4.30 pm to take questions under Standing Order No. 117B (Regional Grand Committees (questions for oral answer)) and to hold a general debate on Building Britain's Future: how the region will make the most of the upturn. —(Mrs. Hodgson.)
The Speaker's opinion as to the decision of the Question being challenged, the Division was deferred until Wednesday 15 July (Standing Order No. 41A).
